# Browser Verification Cleanup

When using MCP/browser checks or starting a temporary dev server:

- Prefer reusing an existing browser page/context when possible; avoid opening extra Chrome/Playwright windows unnecessarily.
- If you open browser tabs/pages/contexts for verification, close them after the check unless the user explicitly asks to keep them open.
- If you start a temporary `npm run dev`/Next server, stop it after the check.
- Before handing off, verify no temporary Next dev process or port you started is still running.
- Do not kill user-started terminals or servers unless the user asks or they are clearly stale blockers from your own verification work.
